ttps://gist.github.com/rain-1/cafbd3b04876cee936802d4d3a9a490d","score":3,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"\u003cp\u003eI made this script because sometimes you want to organize a lot of pictures, and perhaps that could be automated. It seems that the AI models are getting good enough that this sort of works but isnâ€™t perfect.\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"I made this script because sometimes you want to organize a lot of pictures, and perhaps that could be automated. It seems that the AI models are getting good enough that this sort of works but isn't perfect.","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/kae6bd/organize_images_using_ai","submitter_user":"river","user_is_author":true,"tags":["ai"]},{"short_id":"f9vmq0","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/f9vmq0","created_at":"2024-09-25T03:11:49.000-05:00","title":"nanodjango","url":"https://simonwillison.net/2024/Sep/24/nanodjango/","score":19,"flags":0,"comment_count":5,"description":"","description_plain":"","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/f9vmq0/nanodjango","submitter_user":"edoput","user_is_author":false,"tags":["api","python","web"]},{"short_id":"xmt8sh","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/xmt8sh","created_at":"2024-09-25T02:43:18.000-05:00","title":"Whence '\\n'?","url":"https://rodarmor.com/blog/whence-newline/","score":47,"flags":0,"comment_count":11,"description":"","description_plain":"","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/xmt8sh/whence_n","submitter_user":"Hail_Spacecake","user_is_author":false,"tags":["programming","rust"]},{"short_id":"e8gdrw","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/e8gdrw","created_at":"2024-09-25T02:09:39.000-05:00","title":"Comparison of various image captioning models","url":"https://derekphilipau.github.io/image-captioning-model-comparison/","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/e8gdrw/comparison_various_image_captioning","submitter_user":"river","user_is_author":false,"tags":["ai"]},{"short_id":"dtou73","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/dtou73","created_at":"2024-09-24T22:47:46.000-05:00","title":"Declare your AIndependence [includes \"AI bot activity today\" and \"How we find AI bots\"]","url":"https://blog.cloudflare.com/declaring-your-aindependence-block-ai-bots-scrapers-and-crawlers-with-a-single-click/","score":2,"flags":0,"comment_count":3,"description":"","description_plain":"","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/dtou73/declare_your_aindependence_includes_ai","submitter_user":"5d22b","user_is_author":false,"tags":["ai","web"]},{"short_id":"lvrctm","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/lvrctm","created_at":"2024-09-24T22:04:45.000-05:00","title":"Thoughts on Debugging","url":"https://catskull.net/thoughts-on-debugging.html","score":15,"flags":0,"comment_count":7,"description":"","description_plain":"","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/lvrctm/thoughts_on_debugging","submitter_user":"robey","user_is_author":false,"tags":["debugging","practices"]},{"short_id":"37m7tw","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/37m7tw","created_at":"2024-09-24T20:15:10.000-05:00","title":"XKCD 1425 (Tasks) turns ten years old today","url":"https://simonwillison.net/2024/Sep/24/xkcd-1425-turns-ten-years-old-today/","score":38,"flags":0,"comment_count":7,"description":"","description_plain":"","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/37m7tw/xkcd_1425_tasks_turns_ten_years_old_today","submitter_user":"carlana","user_is_author":false,"tags":["ai","practices"]},{"short_id":"t35zfa","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/t35zfa","created_at":"2024-09-24T19:18:24.000-05:00","title":"Persisting PDF annotations server-side","url":"","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"\u003cp\u003eWhile writing a novel, Iâ€™d like to get feedback from alpha and beta readers. Currently, I build a PDF and send an email to each reader individually. A number of readers have requested the ability to send me feedback by adding annotations to the PDF directly. Ideally, without having to install any software on their laptop, desktop, or phone.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDo you know of a super-simple drop-in server-side PHP solution that  allows users to edit PDF files and persist changes? Simplicity is key here:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eintegrates with an existing web server (nginx or apache);\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003euses PHP for handling server-side requests;\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ehas a zero authentication mode (links are always private);\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003edoes not use cloud or SaaS;\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eintegrates with .htaccess files; and\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003euses a flat file system (no SQL database).\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHereâ€™s how I imagine itâ€™d work:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAuthor creates a PDF.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAuthor publishes a PDF to web server.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAuthor sends PDF link to a Reader.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eReader clicks PDF link.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMagic:\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWeb server intercepts PDF link and redirects to PDF editor (e.g., pdf-lib).\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWeb server pre-loads existing annotations from file and adds them to PDF.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eReaderâ€™s browser receives PDF, with any existing annotations added.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eReader annotates PDF.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWeb browser sends annotations to server.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eServer persists annotations in file.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAuthor clicks PDF link, which shows all annotations made so far (by magic).\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf there isnâ€™t such an open-source tool, would anybody be interested if I were to build such a system?\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"While writing a novel, I'd like to get feedback from alpha and beta readers. Currently, I build a PDF and send an email to each reader individually. A number of readers have requested the ability to send me feedback by adding annotations to the PDF directly. Ideally, without having to install any software on their laptop, desktop, or phone.\r\n\r\nDo you know of a super-simple drop-in server-side PHP solution that  allows users to edit PDF files and persist changes? Simplicity is key here:\r\n\r\n* integrates with an existing web server (nginx or apache);\r\n* uses PHP for handling server-side requests;\r\n* has a zero authentication mode (links are always private);\r\n* does not use cloud or SaaS;\r\n* integrates with .htaccess files; and\r\n* uses a flat file system (no SQL database).\r\n\r\nHere's how I imagine it'd work:\r\n\r\n1. Author creates a PDF.\r\n2. Author publishes a PDF to web server.\r\n3. Author sends PDF link to a Reader.\r\n4. Reader clicks PDF link.\r\n5. Magic:\r\n   1. Web server intercepts PDF link and redirects to PDF editor (e.g., pdf-lib).\r\n   2. Web server pre-loads existing annotations from file and adds them to PDF.\r\n   3. Reader's browser receives PDF, with any existing annotations added.\r\n6. Reader annotates PDF.\r\n7. Web browser sends annotations to server.\r\n8. Server persists annotations in file.\r\n9. Author clicks PDF link, which shows all annotations made so far (by magic).\r\n\r\nIf there isn't such an open-source tool, would anybody be interested if I were to build such a system?","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/t35zfa/persisting_pdf_annotations_server_side","submitter_user":"thangalin","user_is_author":true,"tags":["ask","php","programming"]}]